Protesters torched a store and three tractors near
the Moses Mabhida area in Kirkwood in the Eastern Cape. They blocked the R336 road leading to the Moses Mabhida area
with stones and burning tyres. Eastern Cape Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General
Liziwe Ntshinga issued a harsh warning to the violent protesters in Kirkwood. "We view these actions as opportunistic criminal elements that are going to be dealt with harshly," Ntshinga said. It is alleged that a group of about 200 workers blocked
the road with stones dispersed afterward. "At this stage, no case dockets have been opened, but
at least one confirmed orchard store was set alight. Three tractors were also
torched. Currently, the situation is under control and being monitored by
various policing units," the police said. Following that cops
maintained high visibility is in the
area. Motorists were advised to avoid driving towards the Moses
Mabhida area. 